🎨 UI/UX DESIGN (MVP)
🧠 Core UX Principles (FOLLOW STRICTLY)
1 main action per screen
No cognitive overload
Always show progress
Everything feels fast & mobile-first
🖥️ 1. Landing Page (Conversion Focus)
Goal: Turn visitors → paid users
Layout:
🔹 Hero Section

Headline:

“Pass your driving test in 7 days”

Subtext:

AI-powered preparation for Uzbekistan exams

CTA button:
“Start Practice”
🔹 Social Proof
“10,000+ tests taken”
“85% pass rate”
🔹 How It Works (3 steps)
Take a test
AI finds your weak areas
Practice smarter
🔹 Pricing Cards (VERY IMPORTANT)

3 cards:

2 weeks
1 month ⭐ (highlighted)
1 year

👉 Keep it simple + clear

🏠 2. Dashboard (Main Hub)
Goal: Guide user → next action
Layout:
[ Progress Circle: 65% ready ]

[ Weak Topics ]
- Road Signs ❌
- Priority Rules ⚠️

[ Buttons ]
▶ Start Exam
🧠 Practice Weak Areas
📚 Study by Topic
Key UX Ideas:
Show “You are 65% ready to pass”
Always suggest next step
🧪 3. Exam Page (Critical UX)
Goal: Simulate real test
Layout:
[ Timer: 18:45 ]

Question 5/20

[ Question text ]
[ Image if exists ]

( ) Option A  
( ) Option B  
( ) Option C  
( ) Option D  

[ Next ]
UX Rules:
No distractions
One question at a time
Sticky timer
Big tap targets (mobile!)
📊 4. Results Page (MOST IMPORTANT SCREEN)
Goal: Make user continue learning
Layout:
Score: 14/20 ❌

You need 16 to pass

[ Weak Topics ]
- Road Signs (40%)
- Priority Rules (50%)

[ Buttons ]
🧠 Practice Weak Areas (PRIMARY CTA)
🔁 Retake Exam
🔥 Key UX Trick:

Instead of:

“You failed”

Say:

“You’re close — focus on these topics”

🧠 5. Practice Page (AI Magic)
Goal: Feel personalized
Layout:
AI Recommendation:

"Focus on Road Signs today"

[ Start Practice ]

---

Or choose manually:

[ Road Signs ]
[ Priority ]
[ Penalties ]
UX Trick:

Make AI feel smart:

“Based on your last 3 tests…”

📈 6. Progress Page
Goal: Show improvement (addiction loop)
Elements:
Accuracy %
Topics breakdown
Test history
Visual Idea:
Progress bars per topic
Green/red indicators
⚙️ 7. Admin Panel (Simple but powerful)
Pages:
Add Question
Edit Question
Upload Image
Assign Topic
UX Rule:
Fast input (you’ll use this a LOT)
🎨 Design Style (IMPORTANT)
Colors:
Primary: Blue (trust)
Success: Green
Error: Red
Background: Light gray / white
Components:
Rounded cards
Soft shadows
Large buttons
Clean typography
📱 Mobile-First Rules

👉 80% users will be mobile

So:

Big buttons
No small text
Sticky bottom actions
🔥 Key Differentiator UX (Your Secret Weapon)

Add this:

“Daily Plan”

On dashboard:

Today’s Goal:
✔ 1 Practice
✔ 1 Exam

Reward: +10% readiness

👉 This creates habit + retention

❓ Final 2 UX Decisions
Language at launch
A) Uzbek only
B) Uzbek + Russian

👉 I recommend: A first (faster)

Design style
A) Minimal (Duolingo-like, clean)
B) Feature-heavy (more info, more data)

👉 I recommend: A (MUCH better conversion)